sentence: In trading on Friday, shares of Procter & Gamble Company (Symbol: PG) crossed below their 200 day moving average of $89.76, changing hands as low as $89.35 per share.
Procter & Gamble Company shares are currently trading down about 0.6% on the day.

The chart below shows the one year performance of PG shares, versus its 200 day moving average:

Looking at the chart above, PG's low point in its 52 week range is $83.44 per share, with $94.67 as the 52 week high point - that compares with a last trade of $89.58.
According to the ETF Finder at ETF Channel, PG makes up 12.54% of the Consumer Staples Select Sector SPDR Fund ETF (Symbol: XLP) which is trading up by about 0.1% on the day Friday.
